<item>
            <title>[SPARK-28332] SQLMetric wrong initValue </title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-28332</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently SQLMetrics.createSizeMetric create a SQLMetric with initValue set to -1.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If there is a ShuffleMapStage with lots of Tasks which read 0 bytes data, these tasks will send the metric(the metric value still be the initValue with -1) to Driver,  then Driver do metric merge for this Stage in DAGScheduler.updateAccumulators, this will cause the merged metric value of this Stage set to be a negative value. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is incorrect&#65292; we should set the initValue to 0 .&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Another same case in SQLMetrics.createTimingMetric.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
